--
**aLima**

*"Every object remembers. Someone just has to listen."*

You inherited two things from your uncle — who didn't die, but *vanished*: a worn notebook, and a single fragment of an unknown heritage artifact. The notebook's margins are full of signs meant to lead the right person to wherever, or whenever, he has gone.

By day you help run the family junk shop. In the rescued hours, you restore what the scrapyard would melt down.

The week runs five days. When it resets, money and stock vanish — but what you have *learned* never does.

Your till is empty. You start with nothing but the fragment and the notebook.

> Note: in this Twine draft, time is locked to whole hours. In Godot, every 1 real minute = 1 in-game hour (a full 07:00–20:00 day ≈ 13 minutes of real play).

